# Build tooling, docs, and CI are HAND-AUTHORED. openapi-generator's `java` generator scaffolds a full
# Gradle/Maven project (build.gradle, settings.gradle, gradle.properties, the gradle wrapper, README,
# docs, CI). Each is anchored to the project ROOT with a leading slash so it can never overwrite our
# real files — a stub gradle-wrapper.jar clobbering ours is what broke `./gradlew`. The leading slash
# also means the generated CODE under src/main/java/eu/opendppnode/sdk/api is left untouched.
/.github/
/.gitignore
/.travis.yml
/build.gradle
/build.sbt
/git_push.sh
/gradle/
/gradle.properties
/gradlew
/gradlew.bat
/pom.xml
/README.md
/settings.gradle
/api/
/docs/
